data.name: Abstract/Document Error (DL157)
data.summary: The Abstract/Document Error (DL157) IEPD was developed for the California Department of Justice - Data Exchange Project.
data.description: An Abstract/Document Error (DL157) is a form sent from the California Superior Court to the California Department of Motor Vehicles when the court has placed an abstract on an incorrect driving record.  The Department of Motor Vehicles will update their records with the correct information.  The Abstract/Document Error (DL157) contains citation information, driving record information for removal of citation information, signature block.  The Abstract/Document Error (DL157) is one of 44 IEPDs developed by the California Department of Justice - Data Exchange Project to support information exchange between state and local government organizations throughout the state of California.  It could also be adapted for use in other states.

data.name: Escape Notice
data.summary: The Escape Notice IEPD was developed for the California Department of Justice - Data Exchange Project.
data.description:
An Escape Notice is used to notify various agencies if a subject escapes or is captured.  If a subject escapes from jail, the Sheriff notifies the Prosecutor, the Court, and the California Department of Justice.  If a Public Defender respresents a subject and the subject escapes, then the Sheriff notifies the Public Defender of the escape.  If a subject escapes while in local custory and if the subject is under the jurisdiction of the California Department of Corrections and Rehabilitation (CDCR) then the Sheriff notifies the CDCR.  If a subject escapes from the state prison the CDCR informs the Sheriff and the Law Enforcement Agency of the escape.  
If a subject is detained and on probation, and if the subject escapes, the Sheriff notifies the Probation Department of the escape.  
If a subject is captured the CDCR notifies the Sheriff and the Law Enforcement Aency of the capture.  The Escape Notice is one of 44 IEPDs developed by the California Department of Justice - Data Exchange Project to support information exchange between state and local government organizations throughout the state of California.  It could also be adapted for use in other states.

data.name: Health Assessment
data.summary: The Health Assessment IEPD was developed for the California Department of Justice - Data Exchange Project.
data.description: A Health Assessment is sent from the probation department to the youth authority when the court has sentenced a subject to the youth authority and there has been a health assessment conducted on the subject.  The Health Assessment contains subject personal identification information, physical assessment information, and date/time.  The Health Assessment is one of 44 IEPDs developed by the California Department of Justice - Data Exchange Project to support information exchange between state and local government organizations throughout the state of California.  It could also be adapted for use in other states.
